node.text: 1st place from this year's lead Czech Republic Championship on @lezeckastena.bigwall in Prague. There was definitely strange atmosphere because of the limited audience, but even though, the finals was exciting. I enjoyed the end of the route - great setting with the biggest dyno I have ever done on a lead wall. It would be pretty easy dyno on a bouldering wall, but 15 meters above the ground, it felt unnerving, for sure. Great climbing by @konecnik who took the silver, @martin.stranik was third.

node.text:
Adam has successfully arrived in Tokyo and he is already acclimatising with the other athletes in the village. Probably thanks to Pavel's (Adam's physiotherapist) recovery techniques, Adam says he feels "suspiciously good" and it seems like he left the jet leg on the plane this time 😎

Wondering when Adam's first training session is and what time the men's qualification starts? Check out the full current Tokyo Echo on the website 👉 the link is in BIO (the second link)

Disclaimer: During the OG Adam will be solely focusing on his physical and mental preparations for the finals. Therefore all the Tokyo Echoes news is brought to you by his team members. Thank you very much for understanding.

Pics by @pet.phot and @mr_witch666 

AOP Team

#adamondra #AO #tokyoechoes #sportclimbing #climbinginspiration #tokyo2020 #olympijsky #olympics @olympijskytym @olympics @tokyo2020

node.text:
✈ So I'm on my way to Tokyo, where I'll soon be measuring my skills with other great climbers from all over the world in bouldering, lead and speed climbing at the same time. I feel absolutely ready and looking forward to getting to the village 🇯🇵

I and my team, Petr Klofáč - the head coach, and Pavel Vích - my physiotherapist, have chosen a more intimate departure style. Without long time delays, without too many interviews, photos, and videos for media. Special thanks to my fiancée Iva, who accompanied me to Václav Havel Airport in Prague. She is a great support to me. Thanks also to my wolf pack, who were as usual where they should be. Close to me. They even gave me a cool lucky charm - a cute Japanese cat statuette, which might bring me some luck 👏 Even signed by all the people from my team. You can see it in the photo gallery.

I will try to overcome a possible jet lag thanks to Pavel's special care, and I will also try to reprimand coach Petr a bit. He said that the interview for our filmmaker Laco at the airport, which was about 1 sentence long, had been the first and the last one he would give during the whole upcoming competition. So we'll see. 

Don't forget to follow my website, where I'll be posting Tokyo Echoes regularly, and also my Twitter feed, which I've decided to resurrect.

AOP Team

Pics by @pet.phot, who is also heading to Tokyo.

#adamondra #AO #wolfpack #sportclimbing #climbinglife #climbinginspiration #tokyo2020 #olympijsky #olympics @olympijskytym @olympics @tokyo2020

node.text:
Only 2 more days to go! It is a great honor for me to represent 🇨🇿 the Czech Republic at my first Olympic Games. So it was a perfect time to try on the jersey I'll be wearing for the competitions. The Summer Olympics start on Friday, 23 July, and for the first time ever, including lead, bouldering, and speed sport climbing at the same time 💪

Keep an eye on my website www.adamondra.com, the link is in BIO and social media, where I'll be bringing you quick updates and highlights right from the scene and from the Olympic Village as well, where I'll be heading soon.

I can't wait for it! Are you excited too?

Pics by @pet.phot 

#adamondra #AO #sportclimbing #bouldering #climbinglife #climbinginspiration  #olympijsky #olympics @olympijskytym @olympics @tokyo2020

node.text:
When I decided to climb Dawn Wall in 2016, I had barely 1,000 followers on my Instagram. When I came back from the US, I couldn't believe my eyes when 70,000 of you had joined my climbing journey. There are 700,000 of you today. Wow! 😲
 
We want to thank you all for your great support, for that amazing energy. We intend to continue producing videos and other content on the AO website, YouTube channel, Instagram, and Facebook 💪 We are also interested in what content you would appreciate the most? Do you have your own favorites among all those photos and videos?
Let us know in the comments below. Feel free to suggest anything. And last but not least, don't forget to follow Adam Ondra YouTube channel 👉 the link is in BIO. 

We appreciate your interest. Stay tuned. Thank you all once again. 

Adam & Team

#adamondra #outdoorclimbing #outdoorbouldering #rockclimbing #climbinglife #climbinginspiration
#sportclimbing

node.text:
When modern bouldering becomes a challenge, great workout and fun at the same time! 😎 I’ve set the 5-minute timer for each of the 6 boulder problems and tried to climb as many tops as possible! 
The biggest challenge is fast approaching, so I hope that the experience gained from this ultimate boulder training will be super useful to me.

Take a look at the boulder competition simulations in the following video 👉 the link is in BIO. 

Pics by Laco Korbel

#adamondra #AO #sportclimbing #modernboulder #bouldering #boulder #boulderproblem #climber #indoorclimbing #climbinglife #climbinginspiration

node.text:
Check out the new video from my latest La Sportiva visit 🇮🇹 Listen to Pietro Dal Pra and me sharing our thoughts on the importance of climbing shoes. You will get to see the production line as well; you will get to know how many different steps are necessary to make one single shoe 💪

Do you want to see me trying to make a climbing shoe myself? 
Well, let's be honest, I am definitely a better climber than a shoemaker 😅 Enjoy!

Watch the full video on La Sportiva YouTube channel. The link is in BIO. 

Video by @adam_ligocki

#adamondra #AO #LaSportiva #climbingshoes #PietroDalPra #rockclimbing #rockclimber #sportclimbing #climbinginspiration #climbinglife #outdoorclimbing #climber @lasportivagram

node.text:
Anyone who knows me understands that I prefer climbing outside on rocks in connection with nature ⛰ Then there is the world of competitions, thousands of people, media, isolation zone, etc. Competitions on artificial walls cannot be more different. It is a true sport. Measurable, competitive, clear. The Olympic sport. Apart from being a rock climber in my soul, a part of me seeks the challenge when it comes to competitions. To say it straight, it is not like I would feel bad vibes at competitions. The competitive environment is actually not dominated by an unnerving rivalry. I still feel the best among my friends, being outdoors at the crag, as I am definitely an outdoor person, but the people at the contests are also very nice. I like the open competitiveness. In the competition scene, nobody really hides the ambitions to perform well. Yet, there are no enemies 🤜🤛 

In sporting events, competitiveness is a positive thing. Competitions set tremendous challenges. I know months ahead that I must prepare myself for the exact day, for the exact hour. And I must not fail cause I will not be given another chance. 
The world of competitions is... great, actually. And I would be competing all the time. But the fact that my rivals want to beat me tonight in the competition does not change anything about our friendship 🙏

Wanna read more about my own thoughts, check out more photos and get 1 signed postcard free? Enjoy The AO Photo Book, full of pure nature, hard work and emotions, will take you on my two years’ journey around stunning outdoor areas, calm rock formations, as well as pulsating and vibrant indoor contests 💪 The photos are accompanied by my unique texts, where I share thoughts on climbing life, motivation, comfort zone, competitions, climbing etiquette and more.

Choose from 2 variants of the AO Photo Book with or without signature and choose 1 of 4 themes signed postcards for free 👉 the link is in BIO. 

Pics by @lukasbiba and @pet.phot

#adamondra #AObook #climbinginspiration #climbinglife #sportclimbing #bouldering

node.text:
Would you like to find out some secrets hidden behind the production of one of the best climbing shoes in the world? 🌏Why use leather instead of artificial materials? Why do the female models of La Sportiva shoes have the same volume and shape as the male version? 🤔 Find the answers and much more in the article covering a part of my chat with Pietro Dal Pra from La Sportiva 🇮🇹

Visit my website to read about the three shoe models from @lasportivagram , which I’m gonna use at the Olympics 👉 the link is in BIO. 

Hopefully, the shoes will bring me some luck!

#adamondra #AO#climbingshoes #climber #rockclimbing #climbinglife #climbinginspiration #outdoorclimbing #outdoorbouldering #lasportiva #lasportivashoes
#olympics #PietroDalPra

node.text:
It was awesome to be back in HQ of La Sportiva in Val di Fiemme and meet my friend Pietro dal Pra 😎 I joined the La Sportiva team when I was 14 years old and Pietro used to work back then as an athlete manager. Later he joined the research and development team of La Sportiva and he is one of the most important people behind the development of the world's best climbing shoes 🌍 Pietro is also a great friend and amazing climber with whom I did a few adventures, like our trip to Madagaskar or the first free ascent of WoGü in Rätikon. This time, Pietro showed me the production line of climbing shoes, so I had the opportunity to meet the workers there and it was great to find out how much effort and skills of so many people go into one pair of climbing shoes. We also had the time to see the newest prototypes of some pretty sweet, new models for the next season 💪

Pics by @adam_ligocki and @pan_verner from La Sportiva (2021) and Pietro dal Pra from Madagaskar (2010)

#adamondra #AO #lasportiva #lasportivagram #lasportivashoes #rockclimber #rockclimbing #climbinginspiration #climbinglife #outdoorclimbing @lasportivagram

node.text:
When you ask me what kind of climber I am, I feel definitely like a rock climber ⛰ That feeling that rock is my natural habitat has been present since I was a little kid. I need to touch a crag to feel alive. There is a connection between me and rock as soon as I touch its surface. Rock is an energy source that can charge my inner batteries. Climbing a piece of rock is more than just an act of performing moves with my hands and feet.  I feel the power of nature around me when I climb to my limits 👊

Good equipment supports my climbing. It brings me closer to what I really love to do. And what more, it also brings me close to the environments and rocks where I feel free and alive 🌍

Pipe Dream 45 Backpack from Black Diamond is really great support. My team and I use it almost all the time. Take a look at some funny photos from the shooting of the commercial spot for @blackdiamond. I have to appreciate the great work of the team, which gave rise to a beautiful movie.

Watch the full wonderful video, the link is in BIO. 

Pics by @pet.phot

Take a look at one of the simulations in the following video 👉 the link is in BIO.
